Sentencas: We report a freestanding micro solid oxide fuel cell with both the anode and cathode deposited using electrostatic spray deposition (ESD) technique.
Titulo: Freestanding Micro-SOFCs with Electrodes Prepared by Electrostatic Spray Deposition

Sentencas: The cell is consisted of dense yittria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) electrolyte (100nm thick), porous lanthanum strontium manganite (LSM)-YSZ cathode (approximate to 3m thick), and porous NiO-YSZ anode (approximate to 3m thick).
Titulo: Freestanding Micro-SOFCs with Electrodes Prepared by Electrostatic Spray Deposition

Sentencas: LSM-YSZ and NiO-YSZ composite powders were initially prepared by glycine nitrate process and super-critical fluid processes, respectively, and both cathode and anode layers were deposited by the ESD.
Titulo: Freestanding Micro-SOFCs with Electrodes Prepared by Electrostatic Spray Deposition

Sentencas: The resulting freestanding micro cell exhibited an open circuit voltage close to the theoretical value of 1.09V, and a maximum power density of 41.3mWcm(-2) at 640 degrees C.
Titulo: Freestanding Micro-SOFCs with Electrodes Prepared by Electrostatic Spray Deposition
